{"word":"ἐπαγγελία","slug":"ἐπαγγελία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἐπαγγελία, ας, ἡ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐπαγγέλλω\">ἐπαγγέλλω</a></el>] <b>promise,</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ esp.\">esp.</a> associated with God, implicitly or explicitly <b><a href='B:510 2:39'>Ac 2:39</a>; <a href='B:520 4:13'>Ro 4:13f</a>, 20; <a href='B:540 1:20'>2 Cor 1:20</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a>; <el>προσδεχόμενοι τὴν <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀπὸ\">ἀπὸ</a> <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:σοῦ\">σοῦ</a> ἐ.</el> awaiting your promise = waiting for you to say the word <b><a href='B:510 23:21'>Ac 23:21</a>.—</b>With focus on the content of ἐ.: <b><a href='B:490 24:49'>Lk 24:49</a>; <a href='B:510 1:4'>Ac 1:4</a>; <a href='B:510 2:33'>2:33</a>; <a href='B:550 3:14'>Gal 3:14</a>; <a href='B:650 10:36'>Hb 10:36</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐπαγαγεῖν\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐπαγγέλλω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}